  • Constructor Details

    • Animal

      public Animal​(java.lang.String animalImage)
      Method takes in a String variable which is the name of the character image file name within resource path for frog asset. Starts off by setting initial position and adding animation images to the hash maps Character controls are set within this method and based on Node.setOnKeyPressed(EventHandler) and Node.setOnKeyReleased(EventHandler). Key released listener carries out the same actions as key pressed.
      Parameters:
      animalImage - Initializes Frogger Main Character Image.

  • Method Details

    • act

      public void act​(long now)
      Overriden method which is called in every frame as long as AnimationTimer is active. Overriden method constantly checks for checkoutOfBounds(), collisionCheck(), checkCarDeath(), checkWaterDeath() methods.
      Specified by:
      act in class COMP2042_CW_angjiahau.Controllers.Actor
      Parameters:
      now - is the Timestamp of the current frame given in nanoseconds. This value will be the same for all AnimationTimers called during one frame.

    • collisionCheck

      public void collisionCheck()
      Checks if frogger has collided with any objects. Frogger will die and be reset if it has collided with obstacle. If frogger intersects with platform, this method will cause the frogger character to move at the same speed of the platform if isSunk is false. If isSunk if true and frogger is on top of the platform, frogger character will die from waterDeath. If frogger has reached the end(home) and there is already an existing frogger, the deathReset() method will be called. Otherwise, the froggerReachesHome() method will be called.

    • checkCarDeath

      public void checkCarDeath()
      Checks if frogger has collided with car. If carDeath is true, character will not be able to move, media sounds for squashed is called and carDeathAnimation() is called.

    • checkWaterDeath

      public void checkWaterDeath()
      Checks if frogger has died from water. If waterDeath is true, character will not be able to move, media sounds for plunk is called and waterDeathAnimation() is called.

    • froggerReachesHome

      public void froggerReachesHome()
      Carries out actions for when frogger character reaches end point(home). 50 Points are added, yMoved is reset, the end position is filled and frogger returns to starting position.

    • waterDeathAnimation

      public void waterDeathAnimation()
      Plays the animation for when frogger dies from water. deathReset() method is called at the last frame of the animation timeline.

    • carDeathAnimation

      public void carDeathAnimation()
      Plays the animation for when frogger dies from being squashed by an obstacle. deathReset() method is called at the last frame of the animation timeline.

    • addHashCar

      public void addHashCar()
      Adds animation images of car death into the hash map which is called in carDeathAnimation(). Images are fetched from death animation file resource path.

    • addHashWater

      public void addHashWater()
      Adds animation images of car death into the hash map which is called in waterDeathAnimation(). Images are fetched from death animation file resource path.

    • checkWaterHash

      public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​javafx.scene.image.Image> checkWaterHash()
      Used in jUnit test to see if addHashWater() has been carried out successfully, and if HashMap contains the images.
      Returns:
      HashMap of waterDeathAnimation.

    • checkCarHash

      public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​javafx.scene.image.Image> checkCarHash()
      Used in jUnit test to see if addHashCar() has been carried out successfully, and if HashMap contains the images.
      Returns:
      HashMap of carDeathAnimation.

    • deathReset

      public void deathReset()
      Method is called to reset character upon death. startingPosition() is called, initial image of frogger is set, points are deducted by 50 if current points exceeds 50. boolean waterDeath and carDeath are reset.

    • checkoutOfBounds

      public void checkoutOfBounds()
      Checks to see if character has moved out of window.

    • startingPosition

      public void startingPosition()
      Sets character position to same initial position as when round starts.

    • waterLevel

      public void waterLevel​(int waterLevel)
      Setter method to set y-position of waterLevel for each round.
      Parameters:
      waterLevel - Height of water level. Any y-coordinate before this parameter will cause checkWaterDeath() to be true and triggered if character is not on a platform that has isSunk() = false.

    • getStop

      public boolean getStop()
      Sets the number of frogger to be brought home before the round ends.
      Returns:
      Number of frogs to be sent home before round ends.

    • getPoints

      public int getPoints()
      Getter method for points.
      Returns:
      Value of points in the current round.

    • changeScore

      public boolean changeScore()
      Getter method which changes scoreboard to the current points.
      Returns:
      boolean value of changeScore.

    • reset

      public void reset()
      Resets all elements for a fresh start each round. Similar to deathReset(), but resets points and end back to 0. Method is called at the start of each level to ensure that each round is reset.
